<dl id="n12187c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12187c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12187c"> 187(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Suarezian</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">And so successfully does he <font color="green">[Doctor O&apos;Neill]</font> hide any leanings he may have towards one school rather than another, that for all the reader could gather, he might be a Thomist, or a Scotist, or a <mark>Suarezian</mark>. We suspect, however, that he is a philosophical eclectic. <small> John J. Hannon, review of &ldquo;Cosmology&rdquo; <a name="JJHC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JJHC"><cite title="source">Studies</cite></a> (March 1924) 167</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
